113
00:08:07,287 --> 00:08:10,428
at the end of the day, we took to get together

114
00:08:10,448 --> 00:08:11,609
to have a chat.

115
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:15,391
And we decided to replicate that moment

116
00:08:15,631 --> 00:08:18,073
with the Virtual Beer Time to see each other,

117
00:08:18,093 --> 00:08:21,535
to get together, to stay informed.

118
00:08:22,278 --> 00:08:24,039
and answer questions, of course.

119
00:08:25,721 --> 00:08:28,643
We also organized online sessions with a psychologist

120
00:08:28,703 --> 00:08:32,026
for people who feel isolated or overloaded with family.

121
00:08:32,926 --> 00:08:34,448
We improved insurance covering.

122
00:08:35,368 --> 00:08:37,170
We organized a lot of activities,

123
00:08:37,190 --> 00:08:40,332
sport, cooking, gardening activities, online activities.

124
00:08:44,015 --> 00:08:47,178
So I'm very proud that we were able to act quickly

125
00:08:47,258 --> 00:08:48,499
to implement these actions.

126
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,181
But at the end, it was not enough.

127
00:08:51,944 --> 00:08:54,885
How to fix the problem of circulation of information?

128
00:08:54,905 --> 00:08:57,726
How to get to know each other better?

129
00:08:59,426 --> 00:09:02,167
With a studio of approximately 500 experts,

130
00:09:02,947 --> 00:09:04,248
the observation is simple.

131
00:09:05,168 --> 00:09:06,529
The well-being of the employees

132
00:09:07,049 --> 00:09:08,409
and the performance of the studio

133
00:09:08,929 --> 00:09:12,070
cannot rest on the 4 or 5 experts of the upper management.

134
00:09:13,611 --> 00:09:14,391
It's too pressure,

135
00:09:15,431 --> 00:09:16,732
not good for their well-being,

136
00:09:17,752 --> 00:09:20,593
and proves to be unrealistic and ineffective.

137
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:29,897
It was time to put into practice a philosophy we had been thinking about for a couple of years,

138
00:09:31,137 --> 00:09:34,740
an approach based on collective intelligence and accountability.

139
00:09:36,401 --> 00:09:40,303
We needed to move from a standard organization to an ecosystem,

140
00:09:41,024 --> 00:09:44,846
an environment that supports and promotes self-expression.

141
00:09:48,429 --> 00:09:51,751
But don't forget, we were in the middle of a pandemic.

142
00:09:52,924 --> 00:09:55,086
So is it the best time to add major changes?

143
00:09:56,007 --> 00:09:58,849
Indeed, beyond the technical and logistical challenges

144
00:09:58,949 --> 00:10:02,372
of remote work, it was necessary to redefine

145
00:10:02,392 --> 00:10:03,773
the development methods too,

146
00:10:04,994 --> 00:10:07,856
already involving significant changes for everyone.

147
00:10:10,278 --> 00:10:13,360
So again, is now the best time to add major changes?

148
00:10:14,721 --> 00:10:16,222
For us, the answer is yes.

149
00:10:17,584 --> 00:10:18,985
Status quo is not an option.

150
00:10:20,238 --> 00:10:22,080
we have to be true with the studio values,

151
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:26,484
which are people, courage, business savvy,

152
00:10:27,144 --> 00:10:28,405
and continuous improvements.

153
00:10:29,866 --> 00:10:31,628
It was also critical to resolve,

154
00:10:32,348 --> 00:10:35,611
at least reduce our difficulty in detecting problems.

155
00:10:39,694 --> 00:10:42,897
So we began our transition from an organization

156
00:10:42,957 --> 00:10:44,598
based on common policies rules,

157
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:48,561
to a cultural approach based on self-expression.

158
00:10:51,798 --> 00:10:57,261
But we have to start to create a workspace in which experts can express their ideas and opinions.

159
00:10:58,782 --> 00:11:04,425
It may seem surprising, but the biggest challenge in this approach is to deprogram ourselves.

160
00:11:05,946 --> 00:11:12,209
Forget our old reflex of control, hierarchy, old artefacts from the industrial era.

161
00:11:14,070 --> 00:11:20,394
And there is no magic recipe. Everything goes through communication, communication and communication.

162
00:11:21,912 --> 00:11:28,835
Encouragement takes initiative, promoting external and internal initiatives.

163
00:11:30,596 --> 00:11:35,878
It has been key for us to show that it's not just words, but that it's reality and feasible.

164
00:11:37,218 --> 00:11:41,540
So the studio has led by example by putting into practice two initiatives

165
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:48,623
that promote empowerment and autonomy. First, flexibility in working hours.

166
00:11:49,547 --> 00:11:55,630
helping 77% of the employees, and workplace flexibility.

167
00:11:59,232 --> 00:12:02,653
So there is nothing perfect, and it will be a long process,

168
00:12:03,614 --> 00:12:05,234
but there are more and more initiatives,

169
00:12:05,475 --> 00:12:09,076
and the studio management is no longer the only entity

170
00:12:09,116 --> 00:12:11,077
to decide for the studio performance

171
00:12:11,677 --> 00:12:13,398
and EdoScience well-being.

172
00:12:14,799 --> 00:12:17,000
The EdoScience are now more proactive

173
00:12:17,380 --> 00:12:19,021
and create working groups on their own.

174
00:12:19,878 --> 00:12:22,659
and feel encouraged to participate in the life of the studio.

175
00:12:24,539 --> 00:12:27,280
Here are two examples of progress we made.

176
00:12:29,281 --> 00:12:33,302
Example one, as mentioned at the beginning of the presentation,

177
00:12:33,782 --> 00:12:38,123
competition is tough in Quebec. So during a studio meeting,

178
00:12:38,503 --> 00:12:42,384
a virtual beer time, we were discussing the problem

179
00:12:43,004 --> 00:12:48,186
and Edothien decided on the spot to create a retention committee.

180
00:12:49,423 --> 00:12:52,624
