181
00:12:53,364 --> 00:12:57,246
initiating surveys, meetings, and developing proposals.

182
00:12:59,747 --> 00:13:01,928
The good thing about that initiative

183
00:13:02,348 --> 00:13:03,909
is that no one questioned it,

184
00:13:04,789 --> 00:13:07,430
and time, no question the initiative, sorry,

185
00:13:07,530 --> 00:13:10,631
and the time spent by the experts in this committee.

186
00:13:13,032 --> 00:13:13,693
Example two.

187
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:16,814
After we switched to work from home,

188
00:13:17,194 --> 00:13:19,055
we detected a drop of productivity.

189
00:13:20,169 --> 00:13:21,790
Several causes for it.

190
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:26,011
Working remotely, communication channels have multiplied.

191
00:13:27,131 --> 00:13:29,812
Slack, emails, phone, Zoom, Teams, just to name these,

192
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:32,672
causing a lot of disturbance during the day.

193
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:37,654
Boundary between private life and work is now blurred.

194
00:13:39,334 --> 00:13:42,255
But that way is not sustainable in the medium long term.

195
00:13:43,115 --> 00:13:47,096
Stress and fatigue take over, and efficiency, productivity

196
00:13:47,176 --> 00:13:48,117
are greatly reduced.

197
00:13:49,852 --> 00:13:53,873
And like every company, we also face the great resignation.

198
00:13:56,654 --> 00:14:00,355
In this case, collective intelligence has been key.

199
00:14:01,736 --> 00:14:05,177
We all work to propose ideas to improve our efficiency

200
00:14:05,357 --> 00:14:07,117
and question our current methods.

201
00:14:08,798 --> 00:14:09,998
After a month of work,

202
00:14:10,158 --> 00:14:13,559
we decided to start a test with several action points.

203
00:14:16,947 --> 00:14:20,529
which aims to improve studio performance and our well-being,

204
00:14:21,269 --> 00:14:24,971
giving birth to a work program of 32 hours per week

205
00:14:25,051 --> 00:14:25,751
over four days.

206
00:14:28,192 --> 00:14:30,733
Because we all work together to find a solution,

207
00:14:31,113 --> 00:14:34,035
the acceptance rate for this gigantic change

208
00:14:34,095 --> 00:14:35,255
was extremely high.

209
00:14:37,156 --> 00:14:39,837
We monitor the test to learn and adjust, of course.

210
00:14:40,658 --> 00:14:43,339
For example, we know that we are in the right direction,

211
00:14:43,499 --> 00:14:45,320
but there is still work to do.

212
00:14:48,189 --> 00:15:00,596
