00:24:08,688 --> 00:24:09,428
I follow through.

356
00:24:10,129 --> 00:24:12,371
So I didn't mind being a trailblazer

357
00:24:12,511 --> 00:24:13,872
for our black population.

358
00:24:14,853 --> 00:24:16,994
And I loved rolling up my sleeves

359
00:24:17,875 --> 00:24:21,918
and being a part of the Black at PlayStation movement.

360
00:24:22,338 --> 00:24:25,721
And guys, I'm sorry, I, you know, there you go.

361
00:24:32,106 --> 00:24:33,227
The pandemic hits.

362
00:24:34,309 --> 00:24:38,552
It's May 25th, 2020, and George Floyd's death

363
00:24:39,013 --> 00:24:41,034
was a tragedy witnessed by the world.

364
00:24:42,195 --> 00:24:45,218
Now, this was a pivotal moment for Sony and SIE,

365
00:24:45,738 --> 00:24:48,180
and for most corporations across the globe.

366
00:24:49,341 --> 00:24:52,004
You all remember where you were on 9-11

367
00:24:52,304 --> 00:24:54,706
and how you felt watching what happened.

368
00:24:55,547 --> 00:24:57,769
Well, I can tell you the black community

369
00:24:57,869 --> 00:24:59,830
has a similar reaction to May 25th, 2020.

370
00:25:02,105 --> 00:25:06,006
We know what we were doing and how it made us feel watching it.

371
00:25:06,846 --> 00:25:09,607
And sadly, we didn't think anyone

372
00:25:09,687 --> 00:25:13,568
would be held accountable like so many times in our history.

373
00:25:14,828 --> 00:25:18,569
What was unprecedented was Sony and SIE's reaction and support.

374
00:25:20,189 --> 00:25:23,410
There was a movement in external communication.

375
00:25:24,370 --> 00:25:26,971
And SIE posted a statement on Twitter

376
00:25:28,491 --> 00:25:30,432
denouncing systemic racism.

377
00:25:31,868 --> 00:25:33,649
and violence against the black community.

378
00:25:34,550 --> 00:25:37,912
And then they placed the hashtag at the end of that statement.

379
00:25:38,553 --> 00:25:40,514
Hashtag, Black Lives Matter.

380
00:25:41,515 --> 00:25:43,697
Honestly, I thought it was in a parallel universe.

381
00:25:44,357 --> 00:25:45,378
It was extraordinary.

382
00:25:46,299 --> 00:25:50,122
And then a month later, I get a call from the head of DE&I.

383
00:25:51,042 --> 00:25:55,386
She said, Davina, Jim Ryan, who is our CEO,

384
00:25:56,546 --> 00:25:59,509
he would like an audience with the Black App PlayStation

385
00:25:59,969 --> 00:26:00,449
leadership.

386
00:26:01,548 --> 00:26:05,752
We were freaking amazed and I'll put an exclamation point at the end of that.

387
00:26:06,873 --> 00:26:09,596
Jim was attentive and authentic.

388
00:26:10,077 --> 00:26:16,744
He listened to us and surprisingly to those who hear this, Black at PlayStation for the

389
00:26:16,844 --> 00:26:23,751
first time felt like we finally could ask for what we wanted and needed without retribution.

390
00:26:25,492 --> 00:26:27,234
Well, we put a strategy together.

391
00:26:27,715 --> 00:26:28,917
We asked for programs.

392
00:26:29,718 --> 00:26:31,321
We asked for sponsorship.

393
00:26:32,142 --> 00:26:34,486
And we asked for proper funding.

394
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:36,088
And we got it.

395
00:26:36,108 --> 00:26:36,168
Now.

