00:39:20,844 --> 00:39:23,705
in an organization, and it offers structure

586
00:39:24,205 --> 00:39:27,546
on how companies can change their DE&I paradigm

587
00:39:29,547 --> 00:39:31,287
to a merit-worthy practice

588
00:39:31,547 --> 00:39:33,268
that is valued across the company.

589
00:39:34,308 --> 00:39:36,909
And there are two topics from the framework

590
00:39:36,929 --> 00:39:37,889
that I wanna point out.

591
00:39:39,550 --> 00:39:44,954
M stands for make DE&I goals actionable, measurable, evidence-based.

592
00:39:45,755 --> 00:39:47,637
So leaders, they respond to data.

593
00:39:48,357 --> 00:39:48,998
We all agree?

594
00:39:50,359 --> 00:39:55,583
And they should make sure that DE&I goals are inspiring, measurable, and actionable

595
00:39:55,923 --> 00:40:03,430
so that DE&I work that is expected appears attainable by everyone in the organization.

596
00:40:04,270 --> 00:40:05,511
And T stands for...

597
00:40:06,841 --> 00:40:09,623
Work as a core part of the organization

598
00:40:10,104 --> 00:40:11,825
